26#include "config.h"
27#include "WindowOrWorkerGlobalScopeCaches.h"
28
29#include "CacheStorageProvider.h"
30#include "DOMCacheStorage.h"
31#include "DOMWindow.h"
32#include "DOMWindowProperty.h"
33#include "Document.h"
34#include "Frame.h"
35#include "Page.h"
36#include "Supplementable.h"
37#include "WorkerGlobalScope.h"
38
39namespace WebCore {
40
41class DOMWindowCaches : public Supplement<DOMWindow>, public DOMWindowProperty {
42 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
43public:
44 explicit DOMWindowCaches(DOMWindow&);
45 virtual ~DOMWindowCaches() = default;
46
47 static DOMWindowCaches* from(DOMWindow&);
48 DOMCacheStorage* caches() const;
49
50private:
51 static const char* supplementName() { return "DOMWindowCaches"; }
52
53 mutable RefPtr<DOMCacheStorage> m_caches;
54};
55
56class WorkerGlobalScopeCaches : public Supplement<WorkerGlobalScope> {
57 WTF_MAKE_FAST_ALLOCATED;
58public:
59 explicit WorkerGlobalScopeCaches(WorkerGlobalScope&);
60 virtual ~WorkerGlobalScopeCaches() = default;
61
62 static WorkerGlobalScopeCaches* from(WorkerGlobalScope&);
63 DOMCacheStorage* caches() const;
64
65private:
66 static const char* supplementName() { return "WorkerGlobalScopeCaches"; }
67
68 WorkerGlobalScope& m_scope;
69 mutable RefPtr<DOMCacheStorage> m_caches;
70};
71
72// DOMWindowCaches supplement.
73
74DOMWindowCaches::DOMWindowCaches(DOMWindow& window)
75 : DOMWindowProperty(&window)
76{
77}
78
79DOMWindowCaches* DOMWindowCaches::from(DOMWindow& window)
80{
81 auto* supplement = static_cast<DOMWindowCaches*>(Supplement<DOMWindow>::from(&window, supplementName()));
82 if (!supplement) {
83 auto newSupplement = makeUnique<DOMWindowCaches>(window);
84 supplement = newSupplement.get();
85 provideTo(&window, supplementName(), WTFMove(newSupplement));
86 }
87 return supplement;
88}
89
90DOMCacheStorage* DOMWindowCaches::caches() const
91{
92 ASSERT(frame());
93 ASSERT(frame()->document());
94 if (!m_caches && frame()->page())
95 m_caches = DOMCacheStorage::create(*frame()->document(), frame()->page()->cacheStorageProvider().createCacheStorageConnection());
96 return m_caches.get();
97}
98
99// WorkerGlobalScope supplement.
100
101WorkerGlobalScopeCaches::WorkerGlobalScopeCaches(WorkerGlobalScope& scope)
102 : m_scope(scope)
103{
104}
105
106WorkerGlobalScopeCaches* WorkerGlobalScopeCaches::from(WorkerGlobalScope& scope)
107{
108 auto* supplement = static_cast<WorkerGlobalScopeCaches*>(Supplement<WorkerGlobalScope>::from(&scope, supplementName()));
109 if (!supplement) {
110 auto newSupplement = makeUnique<WorkerGlobalScopeCaches>(scope);
111 supplement = newSupplement.get();
112 provideTo(&scope, supplementName(), WTFMove(newSupplement));
113 }
114 return supplement;
115}
116
117DOMCacheStorage* WorkerGlobalScopeCaches::caches() const
118{
119 if (!m_caches)
120 m_caches = DOMCacheStorage::create(m_scope, m_scope.cacheStorageConnection());
121 return m_caches.get();
122}
123
124// WindowOrWorkerGlobalScopeCaches.
125
126ExceptionOr<DOMCacheStorage*> WindowOrWorkerGlobalScopeCaches::caches(ScriptExecutionContext& context, DOMWindow& window)
127{
128 if (downcast<Document>(context).isSandboxed(SandboxOrigin))
129 return Exception { SecurityError, "Cache storage is disabled because the context is sandboxed and lacks the 'allow-same-origin' flag" };
130
131 if (!window.isCurrentlyDisplayedInFrame())
132 return nullptr;
133
134 return DOMWindowCaches::from(window)->caches();
135}
136
137DOMCacheStorage* WindowOrWorkerGlobalScopeCaches::caches(ScriptExecutionContext&, WorkerGlobalScope& scope)
138{
139 return WorkerGlobalScopeCaches::from(scope)->caches();
140}
